One thing which is going to be handy is to be able to identify vowels.  Starting by writing a function for this is a good idea.  It could look like:

    	private boolean isVowel(char c) {
    		return
    			c == &#39;a&#39; || c == &#39;A&#39; ||
    			c == &#39;e&#39; || c == &#39;E&#39; ||
    			c == &#39;i&#39; || c == &#39;I&#39; ||
    			c == &#39;o&#39; || c == &#39;O&#39; ||
    			c == &#39;u&#39; || c == &#39;U&#39;;
    	}

